%N A390983 The smallest prime whose representation in base n contains the digit 0.
%C A390983 If n is prime then a(n) = n, otherwise a(n) > n^2.
%C A390983 Such a prime always exists.
%H A390983 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A390983/b390983.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%t A390983 A390983[n_] := If[PrimeQ[n], n, NestWhile[NextPrime, NextPrime[n^2], FreeQ[IntegerDigits[#, n], 0] &]];
